Sequential steps to create a resource group:

1. Log in to Azure Portal
2. Search for “Resource Groups”
3. Click “Create”
4. Select subscription
5. Enter resource group name
6. Choose region
7. Click “Review + Create”
8. Click “Create”

For example, creating a resource group named “WebApp-RG” for hosting application resources.

A real-life use case is organizing all resources of a project under one group for easy management.

Another example is deleting all resources at once by deleting the resource group.

This exercise builds foundational skills in Azure resource management.
